</span>
$50,000.00 USD</div><div
class="info">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" height="512px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" width="512px"><g><path
d="m256 0c-141.164062 0-256 114.835938-256 256s114.835938 256 256 256 256-114.835938 256-256-114.835938-256-256-256zm121.75 388.414062c-4.160156 4.160157-9.621094 6.253907-15.082031 6.253907-5.460938 0-10.925781-2.09375-15.082031-6.253907l-106.667969-106.664062c-4.011719-3.988281-6.25-9.410156-6.25-15.082031v-138.667969c0-11.796875 9.554687-21.332031 21.332031-21.332031s21.332031 9.535156 21.332031 21.332031v129.835938l100.417969 100.414062c8.339844 8.34375 8.339844 21.824219 0 30.164062zm0 0" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#3041C3"/></g> </svg>
</span>
1 Month</div></div><div
class="how-to-desc"><div
class="how-to-image">
<picture>
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-barbershop-completed-800x800-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="250" height="250" alt="How to Start a Barbershop:">
</picture></div><p>If you are interested in starting your own barbershop, follow our detailed guide below.</p></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=refine-your-idea>Refine your idea.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-existing-barbershops>Research existing barbershops.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-existing-barbershops-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research existing barbershops."></div></div><p>Find out as much as you can about how the big franchises conduct business, what services they offer, and in which ways they are doing things differently.</p><p>Likewise, research smaller, successful, independent shops, and learn about the approach they take to offering their services, marketing their brands, and innovating in the space. Pay attention to business models, supply chains, and quality of service.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=decide-how-you-will-compete>Decide how you will compete.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-decide-how-you-will-compete-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Decide how you will compete."></div></div><p>These days men are seeking more than just a haircut. They are looking for a barbershop experience that is more upscale, includes skincare and hair care services, and a place to socialize, relax, and network.</p><p>There are opportunities for creating hybrids. Some barbershops have coffee shop-style waiting areas and sell clothes or hair care products. There is also a need for quick-service offerings without any frills. Depending on your research into the industry, and what it is you want to achieve, seek a unique approach to what you will offer the market.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section1-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=decide-on-a-business-model>Decide on a business model.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-decide-on-a-business-model-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Decide on a business model."></div></div><p>There are three main business models in the barbershop industry: booth rental, commission, and full-time employment.</p><p><strong>Booth rental</strong> barbershops ask barbers to pay a monthly fee. Essentially, the barbers are independent contractors who rent space in your barbershop.</p><p><strong>The commission model</strong> is a partnership between the owner and individual barber where a percentage of each cut is paid as commission to the barber giving the cut.</p><p>Finally, there's the <strong>full-time employment model</strong>, wherein you employ a barber, pay them a salary, and possibly offer them other benefits.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section1-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=consider-franchising>Consider franchising.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-franchising-is-an-option-288x288-20200817_2020-08-17-144544.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Consider franchising."></div></div><p>Franchises, in some ways, make the process of starting a barbershop easier. They've done the thinking and planning for you. The concept, branding, and business model are already in place, all you need is a location and funding.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section1-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-your-role-in-the-shop>Choose your role in the shop.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-your-role-in-the-shop-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose your role in the shop."></div></div><p>Will you be playing a management role, focusing entirely on running and growing your business, or will you also be cutting hair part time?</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=create-a-barbershop-business-plan>Create a barbershop business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-an-executive-summary>Write an executive summary.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-an-executive-summary-288x288-20200814_2023-09-15-034521_cdxw.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write an executive summary."></div></div><p>Describe what your business will do, write out your mission statement, and explain what makes your business unique.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-ideal-or-current-location>Describe your ideal or current location.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-ideal-or-current-location-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your ideal or current location."></div></div><p>If you do not have a location yet, describe the ideal location you would like for your business. Refer to your market research to show why you would like to work in a particular area.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-launch>Describe your launch.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-launch-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your launch."></div></div><p>State when you would like to launch, if you will be hosting a launch party, and if you are offering opening specials.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=list-your-sources-of-revenue>List your sources of revenue.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-explain-your-source-of-revenue-288x288-20200812.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="List your sources of revenue."></div></div><p>Let investors know how you will be earning money. Your main form of income will be from grooming services, but you could also sell hair and beard products.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=list-your-essential-staff>List your essential staff.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-list-your-essential-staff-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="List your essential staff."></div></div><p>List the job titles of roles you will need to be filled when you launch the business.</p><p>Staff members you may need include:</p><ul><li>Barbers.</li><li>A receptionist.</li><li>Cleaning staff.</li><li>A barista (if you offer coffee).</li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-marketing-strategy>Describe your marketing strategy.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-marketing-strategy-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your marketing strategy."></div></div><p>Explain how you will market your business using social media, flyers, or paid advertisements on Google.</p><p>This section should also include a description of your target market and a summary of your SWOT (strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats) analysis.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=name-and-describe-your-competition>Name and describe your competition.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-name-and-describe-your-competition-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Name and describe your competition."></div></div><p>List at least three barbershops that you have identified as your competition. Describe how they are similar to your business, as well as how your business differs.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-finances>Describe your finances.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-finances-288x288-20200811.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your finances."></div></div><p>List your startup expenses, calculate your break-even point, and include your revenue projections.</p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Download our free barbershop business plan template to find an in-depth guide on writing about your finances. You'll find the template toward the bottom of this page.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section2-step9" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.9&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-future-plans>Describe your future plans.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-describe-your-future-plans-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your future plans."></div></div><p>Discuss how you plan to grow your business. This may include opening another location, selling more products, and/or hiring more staff.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=form-your-barbershop-company>Form your barbershop company.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-legal-entity>Create a legal entity.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-business-structures-288x288-20200820_2023-09-15-035500_nxnj.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a legal entity."></div></div><p>Forming a business entity protects you from liability and can save you money on taxes. You have four possible legal structures to choose from for your barbershop: sole proprietorship, partnership, limited liability company, or a corporation.</p><p><strong>Most barbershop owners choose LLC.</strong> This structure protects you from personal liability. LLC's are more flexible when it comes to taxes, but can be difficult to set up.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-name>Choose a name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/trademark-your-name-288x288-20200619.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a name."></div></div><p>Create name ideas with a <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/">business name generator</a> and narrow down your choices by asking potential customers for feedback.</p><p>Once you have chosen a name, take it one step further and protect your business's name and logo with a trademark.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-your-company>Register your company.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-your-company-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register your company."></div></div><p>File a DBA (doing business as), or file LLC paperwork with the State, and register a trademark, if necessary.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section3-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=get-an-employer-identification-number>Get an Employer Identification Number (EIN).</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-an-employer-identification-number-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Get an Employer Identification Number (EIN)."></div></div><p>An EIN, or Federal Tax Identification Number, is assigned by the IRS to businesses. If you employ staff members, you are required to have an EIN.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section3-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-legal-and-financial-basics>Set up legal and financial basics.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-open-a-business-bank-account-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up legal and financial basics."></div></div><p>Opening a business bank account that is separate from your personal accounts protects you from liability and gives you access to business banking services. You should also consider buying business insurance to protect your business from losses caused by lawsuits, fire, flood, theft, etc.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=find-funding>Find funding.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-funding-options>Research funding options.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-funding-options-288x288-20200818_2023-09-15-040011_lctu.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research funding options."></div></div><p>To get set up and have the products and equipment you need to run your barbershop for the first few months, you'll need a substantial sum of money, which can come from a financial backer.</p><p><strong>There are two main types of financing models available to small business owners.</strong> Debt financing is what banks, government programs, and money lenders offer. The business owner will have a certain amount of time to repay the loan with interest.</p><p><strong>Equity financing</strong> is what investors offer. It is money they pay into the business for a stake in the business.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=approach-banks-for-a-loan>Approach banks for a loan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-open-a-business-bank-account-288x288-20200818_2023-09-15-040104_kkhi.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Approach banks for a loan."></div></div><p>A small business loan is the most common way to finance a new business, so you should approach several banks to find out about their loan programs.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-a-business-credit-card>Apply for a business credit card.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-business-credit-card-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for a business credit card."></div></div><p>A business credit card can help to cover day-to-day costs that can easily be repaid.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section4-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=research-small-business-grants>Research small business grants.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-small-business-grants-288x288-20200824.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Research small business grants."></div></div><p>There are a number of grants available for small businesses. Research grants for the personal grooming industry or general small business grants offered by the government or private organizations.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=find-a-location>Find a location.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=think-about-your-target-market-and-needs>Think about your target market and needs.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-think-about-your-target-market-and-needs-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Think about your target market and needs."></div></div><p>There is a lot to consider when deciding on a location for your barbershop. Depending on your budget and the nature of your barbershop, you will be looking for certain characteristics that boost brand identity, attract your target market, and elevate chances of growth and success.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section5-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=check-that-your-location-meets-requirements>Check that your location meets requirements.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-consider-board-requirements-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Check that your location meets requirements."></div></div><p>There are state cosmetology and barbering board requirements when it comes to setting up your barbershop, and it is important you make sure to comply with them.</p><p><strong>Barbershop facility requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Hot and cold running water.</li><li>Public bathrooms.</li><li>Drinking water.</li><li>Containers for trash and soiled items.</li><li>Cabinets that close properly.</li><li>At least 35 square feet around each barber chair.</li></ul></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section6" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>6.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=set-up-your-barbershop>Set up your barbershop.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section6-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=design-the-layout-of-your-barbershop>Design the layout of your barbershop.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-design-the-layout-of-barbershop-288x288-20230926.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Design the layout of your barbershop."></div></div><p>The design and layout of your barbershop and the furniture and decorations you choose are entirely up to you. If you want a minimalist feel, less is more. If you want to throw back to the 1950s, or even further, to the Wild West, antiques are a must.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section6-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=put-essential-software-in-place>Put essential software in place.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-put-software-in-place-288x288-20230926.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Put essential software in place."></div></div><p>There are various types of software you can get to ensure the smooth running of your business.</p><ul><li><strong>Accounting software</strong> tracks business finances (expenses, debt, credit, tax, etc.).</li><li><strong>Inventory software</strong> helps track everything a barbershop needs to run effectively.</li><li><strong>Salon management software</strong> will help schedule and manage appointments, process sales and payments, and manage client information.</li><li><strong>Point-of-sale (POS) software</strong> allows businesses to accept a variety of payments for services and products and tracks sales.</li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section6-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=secure-suppliers>Secure suppliers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-secure-suppliers-288x288-20230926.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Secure suppliers."></div></div><p>A barbershop requires a lot of equipment, some of which need to be replaced constantly. Find a supplier for razors, clippers, styling gels, cleaners, sterilizers, etc., one that is affordable, timely, and has high-quality supplies.</p><p>You can buy supplies online, where there is generally a greater selection and lower prices. Alternatively, buy supplies from your local retailer, who might be able to deliver faster.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section7" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>7.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=build-your-team>Build your team.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section7-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=recruit-qualified-barbers>Recruit qualified barbers.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-recruit-qualified-barbers-288x288-20230926.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Recruit qualified barbers."></div></div><p>A good team will make your shop a success. Whether you employ full-time barbers, strike a commission-based deal, or charge booth rent, you should still aim to have only the best barbers you can find working in your barbershop. Each of them must have a barber's license.</p><p>Use social media, job boards, word-of-mouth, and staffing agencies to help you attract and hire the best applicants.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section7-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=draft-basic-employment-contracts>Draft basic employment contracts.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-draft-contracts-288x288-20230926.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Draft basic employment contracts."></div></div><p>Your barbershop will need a set of basic contracts; an employment contract is essential. Have a lawyer put one together or find one online.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section8" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>8.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=market-your-barbershop>Market your barbershop.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-barbershop-section8-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-a-domain-name-and-create-a-website>Register a domain name and create a website.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-website-288x288-20230926.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register a domain name and create a website."></div></div><p>Before creating a website, <a
href="https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-register-a-domain-name">register a domain name</a> for your barbershop with a domain name registrar. Next, create a user-friendly, informative website that is perfectly aligned with your brand.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
